projects.name: Haus TF
projects.briefDescription: Single‑family house in the UNESCO‑protected Neusiedler See landscape, set between forest and vineyard. The design balances contemporary expression with vernacular character: untreated larch and locally sourced stone reinforce regional identity, while generous openings frame vineyard views and connect interiors to the landscape.

projects.name: ‘OPUS’ Bar — Ivan Vazov
projects.briefDescription: A demountable steel “umbrella” shelters an urban terrace year-round with a light, reversible footprint in a heritage setting. Spanning 557m², it integrates lighting/sound and ties into existing utilities. A 5m² bar wraps a masonry core with storage and WCs. Polycarbonate sliders and fabric curtains open/close seasonally; deep eaves extend cover for ~400 guests

projects.name: Horses for the Historic Carriage
projects.briefDescription: The installation leverages controlled reflections across curved metal surfaces to create a convincing illusion of movement without mechanical parts or multimedia. The minimal composition frames the carriage, preserves clear sightlines, and heightens the visitor’s immediate, kinetic reading of the object. | © d*a

projects.name: Blue Porcelain Collection — Esterházy Castle
projects.briefDescription: Within the Treasury of 13th-century Castle, blue porcelain rests on gold-plated plinths cantilevered from structural glass fins set in compacted sand, making objects appear to hover. Restored wall paintings and limestone flooring remain; gaps are stitched with slender brass inlay. Services conceal behind a gold-plated sculptural door, turning maintenance into a deliberate feature.

projects.name: Pathway Over the Mountain
projects.briefDescription: Reuse of historic sidewalk stones, gravestones and cuboids (originally supplied by the City of Vienna to the St. Margarethen sculptor symposia) to create a walkable, climb-assisting landscape that links the parking area to the “path over the mountain.”

projects.name: Anklavs
projects.briefDescription: A compact plan maximizing space value; a split-level roof forms a semi-sheltered terrace. Inside, a continuous built-in surface becomes desk, bed, oven and storage, softly zoning a cork-lined meditation/yoga area. A material palette of thatch, cob, cork, and timber: breathable, durable, and low-maintenance.

projects.name: Monsieur George — Boutique Hotel
projects.briefDescription: Interior design and delivery support for a boutique hotel in Paris, focusing on coordinated drawing packages (GA, RCP, M&E), FF&E and finishes, with procurement-ready schedules and manufacturer liaison to take bespoke elements through to production.

projects.name: Apple Marunouchi
projects.briefDescription: In Tokyo’s Marunouchi district beside Tokyo Station. The tower’s perimeter grid forms two-storey glass vitrines framed in specially cast aluminium with 3D-radiused corners. Inside, a double-height forum linked by a sculptural white-steel stair with terrazzo treads. | © F+P
